  "title": "M&E Resident Technical Officer (RTO / Pharmaceutical Projects)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p><strong>1. Drawing Interpretation & Design Coordination</strong></p><ul><li>Deep understanding of construction drawings, schematics, SLDs, and layout plans.</li><li>Proactively identify design conflicts or issues on-site and coordinate with designers for resolution.</li><li>Support RFIs and constructability reviews with the design team.</li></ul><p><strong>2. Regulatory Compliance & Submission Support</strong></p><p>Familiar with and apply key local codes such as:</p><ul><li>SCDF (Fire Protection/FSSD submissions)</li><li>PUB (Plumbing, condensate, chilled water drainage)</li><li>NEA (Exhaust systems, chemical handling)</li><li>Assist in preparing compliance documentation and test plans for FSC and TOP submissions.</li></ul><p><strong>3. Site Supervision & Quality Control</strong></p><ul><li>Supervise key installations including HVAC, fire protection, process piping, electrical, and control systems.</li><li>Review material deliveries, installation quality, and documentation to ensure conformance.</li><li>Support and witness SAT, TAB, and functional performance tests.</li></ul><p><strong>4.Coordination & Documentation</strong></p><ul><li>Maintain daily site diary, photo records, NCR logs, and rectification tracking.</li><li>Attend coordination meetings with contractors, designers, and client to resolve technical issues.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma/Degree in engineering Mechanical / Electrical / Facility / Civil Engineering. </li><li><strong>MUST be registered M&E RTO under BCA Singapore. </strong></li><li>Minimum 10 years of site experience with pharmaceutical or GMP projects experiences.</li><li>Strong abilities to read and interpret M&E drawings; experience in technical clarifications (RFI) is a plus.</li><li>Knowledge of SCDF, PUB, NEA submission and approval processes is required.</li><li>Familiar with FSC testing, TOP submission flow, and common system testing requirements.</li><li>Good time management, project handling, and communication skills. </li></ul><p><br />GMP Technologies (S) Pte Ltd | EA Licence 11C3793 | EA Personnel: Novita Widjaja | Registration No: R22105960</p><p><em>This is in partnership with the Employment and Employability Institute Pte Ltd (“e2i”).</em></p><p><em>e2i is the empowering network for workers and employers seeking employment and employability solutions. e2i serves as a bridge between workers and employers, connecting with workers to offer job security through job-matching, career guidance and skills upgrading services, and partnering employers to address their manpower needs through recruitment, training, and job redesign solutions. e2i is a tripartite initiative of the National Trades Union Congress set up to support nation-wide manpower and skills upgrading initiatives.</em></p><p><em>By applying for this role, you consent to GMP Recruitment Services (S) Pte Ltd’s </em><a href=\"https://www.gmprecruit.com/legal/privacy-policy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">PDPA</a><em> and </em><a href=\"https://us-west-2.protection.sophos.com?d=e2i.com.sg&u=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZTJpLmNvbS5zZy9wZHBhLw==&i=NThlNDdhOGMyYmI5N2YwZmQxZDk4NjQw&t=cWdqRFV0Uy80RjN3MDlSYmM1dS85VTRxVTRoYVlXdWFyWTYzaGlVS3k0TT0=&h=1ad0460f503340658fbeab159c31256f&s=AVNPUEhUT0NFTkNSWVBUSVaVGQEVMuPAipiPENS4aadnRg3RqoiWpHBKgNtumWhHjA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em>e2i’s PDPA</em></a><em>.</em></p>",
